<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2374/98 of 3 November 1998 concerning the authorisation of new additives in feedingstuffs (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2374/98 teatavate s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandite lubamise kohta 3. november 1998 (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 70/524/EEC of 23 November 1970 concerning additives in feedingstuffs (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 98/19/EC (2), and in particular Articles 9j and 3 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandeid k&auml;sitlevat n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1970. aasta direktiivi 70/524/EM&Uuml; (1) (viimati muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 98/19/E&Uuml; (2)), eesk&auml;tt selle artikleid 9j ja 3, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Directive 70/524/EEC lays down that new additives or new additive uses may be authorised in line with advances in scientific and technical knowledge; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivis 70/524/EM&Uuml; n&auml;hakse ette, et teaduse ja tehnika edusamme arvesse v&otilde;ttes v&otilde;ib lubada kasutada uusi s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandeid ja rakendada s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandite uusi kasutusviise; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Directive 93/113/EC (3), as last amended by Directive 97/40/EC (4), by derogation from Directive 70/524/EEC, authorised Member States to permit provisionally the use and marketing of enzymes, micro-organisms and their preparations in animal nutrition; </inglise>
<eesti> erandina direktiivist 70/524/EM&Uuml; v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 93/113/E&Uuml; (3) (viimati muudetud direktiiviga 97/40/E&Uuml; (4)) kohaselt ajutiselt lubada ens&uuml;&uuml;mide, mikroorganismide ja neid sisaldavate valmististe kasutamist loomas&ouml;&ouml;tades ning nende turustamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas examination of the dossiers, submitted by the Member States in accordance with Article 3 of Directive 93/113/EC, indicates that a certain number of substances in the groups of enzymes and micro-organisms can be provisionally authorised; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 93/113/E&Uuml; artikli 3 kohaselt esitatud liikmesriikide toimikute l&auml;bivaatamine on n&auml;idanud, et teatava arvu ens&uuml;&uuml;mide ja mikroorganismide gruppi kuuluvate ainete kasutamist v&otilde;ib ajutiselt lubada;. </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Scientific Committee for Animal Nutrition has delivered a favourable opinion with regard to the harmlessness of these substances; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee on andnud soodsa hinnangu nende ainete kahjutuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Feedingstuffs, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise s&ouml;&ouml;dakomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The substances belonging to the group 'Enzymes' and listed in the Annex to this Regulation may be authorised according to Directive 70/524/EEC as additives in animal nutrition under the conditions laid down in that Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Koosk&otilde;las direktiiviga 70/524/EM&Uuml; v&otilde;ib ens&uuml;&uuml;mide gruppi kuuluvaid k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas loetletud aineid lubada s&ouml;&ouml;dalisanditena kasutada selles lisas etten&auml;htud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kahek&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 July 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse alates 1. juulist 1999. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. Done at Brussels, 3 November 1998. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Franz FISCHLER Member of the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 3. november 1998 </eesti>
